Built with Ruby, Installed with DEFAULT RUBY. (default ruby recomended) 

DEFAULT RUBY = requires you to use SUDO when intalling GEMS. 

# Xcode 9 + 10
$ sudo gem install cocoapods

list the dependencies in a TEXT file named PODFILE in Xcode. 

{ 

platform :ios, '8.0'
use_frameworks!

target 'MyApp' do
  pod 'AFNetworking', '~> 2.6'
  pod 'ORStackView', '~> 3.0'
  pod 'SwiftyJSON', '~> 2.3'
end

}

cocoapods provides a POD INIT command to create a PODFILE with smart defaults (USE IT)

Import your dependencies e.g. 

{

<Reachability/Reachability.h>

}
